<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,366,1088]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,325,482,508]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[334,466,482,507]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophomilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albistria">
<emphasis box="[334,466,482,507]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">L. albistria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[483,626,482,508]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 24" captionStartId="7.[151,274,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[190,1381,229,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,199,1759]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 24. Lophomilia spp., adults. 17. L. kogii, male, Russia, Primorye terr. Khasansky distr., Andreevka (FNM); 18. L. albicosta, male, China, Tapai-Shan (ZFMK); 19. L. albistria, male, Nepal, Kathmandu, Pulchouki Mt. (ZSM); 20. L. albistria, female, Nepal, Pulchouki Mt. (ZSM); 21. L. kobesi, male, holotype, Indonesia, Sumatra (ZSM); 22. L. kobesi, female, paratype, Indonesia, Sumatra (ZSM); 23. L. violescens, holotype, male, Nepal, Godavari (after Yoshimoto, 1993); 24. Hepatica anceps, syntype, Russia, “ Sutschan ” (MNHU)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274661/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Figs. 
<number box="[550,626,482,508]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="19.2">19, 20</number>
</figureCitation>
) is similar to the 
<taxonomicName box="[836,988,482,507]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophomilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flaviplaga">
<emphasis box="[836,988,482,507]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">L. flaviplaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group in wing coloration and ground plan of wing pattern, but differs by the less strongly expressed pattern, absence of yellow patch between antemedial and subterminal lines, and the smaller but more conspicuous white bar mark dorsally on postmedian line. Wingspan 
<quantity box="[480,611,598,624]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" unit="mm" value="27.5" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="27.0">27–28 mm</quantity>
. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[809,895,598,624]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 39" captionStartId="17.[151,269,1781,1805]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,197,1756]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,197,1757]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 39. Lophomilia spp. and Hepatica anceps, adults and male genitalia. 33. L. striatipurpurea, imago (after Holloway 1976); 34. L. striatipurpurea, male genitalia (after Holloway 1976); 35. L. albicosta, China, Tapaishan, prep. 2093 VK ZFMK; 36. L. kobesi, holotype, prep. 6540 GB, Indonesia, Sumatra (ZSM); 37. L. violescens, holotype, Nepal (after Yoshimoto 1993); 38. L. albistria, prep. 6526 GB, Nepal, Kathmandu, Pulchouki Mt. (ZSM); 39. Hepatica anceps, Russia, Primorye terr. prep. AM ZISP." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274664/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[864,895,598,624]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="38.0">38</number>
</figureCitation>
) characterized by narrow elongate valva with unexpressed costa and longitudinal position of clasper-harpe complex, which is long, extending almost to apex of valva; juxta wide at bottom with a ventral prominence, bearing a caudally projected long process at middle. Most conspicuous character is the structure of sacculus, with long and stout asymmetrical saccular projection (left segment slender and bent near tip). Aedeagus slightly curved; vesica with a row of short and stout cornuti near base. In female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[665,751,792,818]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 49" captionStartId="18.[151,269,1778,1802]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,228,1726]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,194,1754]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 49. Lophomilia spp. and Hepatica anceps, female genitalia. 40. L. flaviplaga, South Korea, prep. 250 - 2 d HL CIS; 41. L. takao, China, Yunnan, prep. VK NEFU; 42. L. diehli; paratype, prep. 6538 GB, Indonesia, Sumatra; 43. L. polybapta, China, China, Yunnan, prep. VK NEFU; 44. L. nekrasovi sp. n. China, Tapaishan, prep. 2032 VK ZFMK; 45. L. rustica, China, Tapaishan, prep. 2087 VK ZFMK; 46. L. hoenei, China, Yunnan, prep. 2102 VK ZFMK; 47. L. kogii, South Korea, prep. 231 - 2 c HL CIS; 48. L. albistria, prep. 6526 GB, Nepal, Kathmandu, Pulchouki Mt.; 49. H. anceps, South Korea, prep. 255 - 2 HL CIS." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274665/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[720,751,792,818]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="48.0">48</number>
</figureCitation>
) ovipositor wide, papillae anales quadrangular; apophyses anteriores two times shorter than posterior ones; antrum wide, sclerotised, shallow; ductus bursae short, sclerotised; bursa copulatrix elongate, heavily sclerotised in caudal part, with wide sclerotised cervix, membranous in proximal part, without signum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,366,1088]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,547,946,972]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Distribution and biology.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[566,666,946,972]" captionStart="FIGURES 58 – 62" captionStartId="20.[151,270,1495,1519]" captionTargetBox="[193,1394,162,1465]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,155,1471]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 58 – 62. Lophomilia spp., distribution maps. 58. L. albistria; 59. L. violescens; 60. L. striatipurpurea; 61. L. diehli; 62. L. kobesi." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274667/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[629,666,946,972]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="58.0">58</number>
</figureCitation>
). Central 
<collectingCountry box="[785,859,946,972]" name="Nepal" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Nepal</collectingCountry>
. Adults have been collected in March (
<number box="[1329,1390,946,972]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1.22">
1, 
<date box="[1357,1390,946,972]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">22</date>
</number>
.iii), April (
<number box="[229,290,985,1011]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2.12">
2, 
<date box="[258,290,985,1011]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">12</date>
</number>
.iv), June (
<date box="[411,470,985,1011]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<number box="[411,440,985,1011]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="11.0">11</number>
.vi
</date>
) 
<date box="[486,660,985,1011]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1990" valueMax="1992">
<number box="[486,545,985,1011]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1990.0">1990</number>
and 
<number box="[601,660,985,1011]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</date>
(
<typeStatus box="[674,726,985,1011]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">type</typeStatus>
series), July and late August (
<collectionCode box="[1077,1139,985,1011]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/4b7r-7sec" name="Bavarian State Collection of Zoology" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">ZSM</collectionCode>
material) at elevations of 
<quantity box="[151,321,1024,1050]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" unit="m" value="1500.0" valueMax="1800.0" valueMin="1200.0">1200–1800 m</quantity>
, at Mt. Pulchouki near Godavari village, vicinity of Kathmandu. Probably bivoltine, moths occuring in hillside broadleaved forest. The larvae and foodplants are unknown.
</paragraph>
